title: Clay Travis and Buck Sexton Show H1 - Dec 23 2021
itunes:title: Clay Travis and Buck Sexton Show H1 - Dec 23 2021
description:
Supreme Court is going to hear a challenge to Biden's covid mandates. Clay predicts a good chance SCOTUS will strike it down. Good news: Clay's studying of reports suggests Omicron variant milder though more contagious. FDA authorizes second pill against COVID-19 symptoms. Biden "ooooh, don't tempt me" says he wants to run against Trump in 2024. Kamala Harris, who was picked to be VP because she’s a black woman, is now complaining that she’s being treated unfairly by the media because she’s not a white man. Democrat heavyweight Stacey Abrams, who never admitted defeat, makes another run at Georgia governor.
